00170 //! Calcule la conductivite
00171 void Loi_Etat_GP_base::calculer_lambda()
00172 {
00173   const Champ_Don& mu = le_fluide->viscosite_dynamique();
00174   const DoubleTab& tab_mu = mu.valeurs();
00175   Champ_Don& lambda = le_fluide->conductivite();
00176   DoubleTab& tab_lambda =lambda.valeurs();
00177 
00178   int i, n=tab_lambda.size();
00179 
00180 // La conductivite est soit un champ uniforme soit calculee a partir de la viscosite dynamique et du Pr
00181   if (sub_type(Champ_Fonc_Tabule,lambda.valeur()))
00182     {
00183       lambda.valeur().mettre_a_jour(temperature_.valeur().temps());
00184       return;
00185     }
00186   if (!sub_type(Champ_Uniforme,lambda.valeur()))
00187     {
00188       if (sub_type(Champ_Uniforme,mu.valeur()))
00189         {
00190           double mu0 = tab_mu(0,0);
00191           for (i=0 ; i<n ; i++) tab_lambda(i,0) = mu0 * Cp_ / Pr_;
00192         }
00193       else
00194         {
00195           for (i=0 ; i<n ; i++) tab_lambda(i,0) = tab_mu(i,0) * Cp_ / Pr_;
00196         }
00197     }
00198   else
00199     {
00200       if (sub_type(Champ_Uniforme,mu.valeur()))
00201         {
00202           tab_lambda(0,0) = mu(0,0) * Cp_ / Pr_;
00203         }
00204       else
00205         {
00206           Cerr << finl ;
00207           Cerr << "If lambda is of type Champ_Uniform, mu must also be of type Champ_Uniforme !"<< finl;
00208           Cerr << "If needed, you can use a Champ_Fonc_Fonction or a Champ_Fonc_Tabule with a constant for mu."<< finl ;
00209           Cerr << finl ;
00210           Process::exit();
00211         }
00212     }
00213   tab_lambda.echange_espace_virtuel();
00214 }

00229 //! Calcule la diffusivite
00230 void Loi_Etat_GP_base::calculer_alpha()
00231 {
00232   const Champ_Don& lambda = le_fluide->conductivite();
00233   const DoubleTab& tab_lambda = lambda.valeurs();
00234   Champ_Don& alpha=le_fluide->diffusivite();
00235   DoubleTab& tab_alpha = le_fluide->diffusivite().valeurs();
00236   const DoubleTab& tab_rho = le_fluide->masse_volumique().valeurs();
00237 
00238   int isVDF=0;
00239   if (alpha.valeur().que_suis_je()=="Champ_Fonc_P0_VDF") isVDF = 1;
00240   int i, n=tab_alpha.size();
00241 
00242   if (isVDF)
00243     {
00244       if (sub_type(Champ_Uniforme,lambda.valeur()))
00245         {
00246           double lambda0 = tab_lambda(0,0);
00247           for (i=0 ; i<n ; i++) tab_alpha(i,0) = lambda0 / (tab_rho(i,0) * Cp_);
00248         }
00249       else
00250         {
00251           for (i=0 ; i<n ; i++) tab_alpha(i,0) = tab_lambda(i,0) / (tab_rho(i,0) * Cp_);
00252         }
00253     }
00254   else
00255     {
00256       const IntTab& elem_faces=ref_cast(Zone_VF,le_fluide->vitesse().zone_dis_base()).elem_faces();
00257       double rhoelem;
00258       int face, nfe = elem_faces.line_size();
00259       if (sub_type(Champ_Uniforme,lambda.valeur()))
00260         {
00261           double lambda0 = tab_lambda(0,0);
00262           for (i=0 ; i<n ; i++)
00263             {
00264               rhoelem=0;
00265               for (face=0; face<nfe; face++) rhoelem += tab_rho(elem_faces(i,face),0);
00266               rhoelem /= nfe;
00267               tab_alpha(i,0) = lambda0 / ( rhoelem * Cp_ );
00268             }
00269         }
00270       else
00271         {
00272           for (i=0 ; i<n ; i++)
00273             {
00274               rhoelem=0;
00275               for (face=0; face<nfe; face++) rhoelem += tab_rho(elem_faces(i,face),0);
00276               rhoelem /= nfe;
00277               tab_alpha(i,0) = tab_lambda(i,0) / ( rhoelem * Cp_ );
00278             }
00279         }
00280     }
00281   tab_alpha.echange_espace_virtuel();
00282 }

00284 double Loi_Etat_GP_base::calculer_masse_volumique(double P, double T) const
00285 {
00286   if (inf_ou_egal(T,0))
00287     {
00288       Cerr << finl << "Error, we find a temperature of " << T << " !" << finl;
00289       Cerr << "Either your calculation has diverged or you don't define" << finl;
00290       Cerr << "temperature in Kelvin somewhere in your data file." << finl;
00291       Cerr << "Check your data file." << finl;
00292       Process::exit();
00293     }
00294   return P / ( R_ * T );
00295 }
